WEBVTT

00:02.736 --> 00:06.140
What did you say?
"Pass the peas and
I'm dropping out of college"?

00:06.174 --> 00:10.178
No, I said, "Pass the peas,
please. And I have
withdrawn from college."

00:10.211 --> 00:14.248
She said "please."
Pass her the peas.

00:14.282 --> 00:16.517
I believe we paid for four
years of college.

00:16.550 --> 00:20.588
Since I finished college,
I can count.
You attended three.

00:20.621 --> 00:23.524
- Yes, ma'am.
I'm gonna skip the fourth.
- Is that right? You got a job?

00:23.557 --> 00:27.261
-Sort of.
-The line between "sort of" and
"yes" don't meet in the middle.

00:27.295 --> 00:29.530
Do you have a job?

00:29.563 --> 00:32.200
I will.
She will.

00:32.233 --> 00:35.703
You got a memory?
Or did you lose that
with your common sense?

00:35.736 --> 00:40.341
I recall you coming
home from school,
wanting to drop out.

00:40.374 --> 00:44.078
- You made us a deal.
- Yes, and the deal was
I'd try.

00:44.112 --> 00:46.380
I'll try means I'll fail.

00:46.414 --> 00:48.949
You know that.
Is that what we're looking at?

00:48.982 --> 00:51.752
Are you gonna sit there and eat
or are you gonna talk
to this wild child?

00:51.785 --> 00:54.088
She seems opposed to dialogue.

00:56.157 --> 00:59.093
You have one more year.
You'll have a degree.

00:59.127 --> 01:02.096
You can choose whatever you--
I made my choice, Mom.

01:15.276 --> 01:17.911
She's enlisted.

01:35.829 --> 01:39.333
If I were you,
I'd clean my plate.

01:39.367 --> 01:42.002
She's not ready.
She isn't?

01:42.035 --> 01:45.573
- Or you aren't?
- There's a war, Jonas.

01:45.606 --> 01:48.342
You've lived your life
in the military.

01:48.376 --> 01:50.511
I thought you'd be prepared
for this, time came.

01:50.544 --> 01:54.448
I wasn't prepared the first day
she went to kindergarten.

01:56.384 --> 02:00.321
I wasn't prepared...

02:00.354 --> 02:02.290
first time
she got her heart broken.

02:05.626 --> 02:09.330
- Fix it.
- Wouldn't if I could.

02:09.363 --> 02:12.099
You want your daughter
to go to war?

02:12.132 --> 02:14.202
What I want is my daughter
to tackle...

02:14.235 --> 02:19.340
whatever she decides to do
with commitment and honor.

02:19.373 --> 02:24.478
As a military wife, I am proud
my husband serves this country,

02:24.512 --> 02:29.450
but there's a big disconnection
between military wife...

02:29.483 --> 02:34.655
and mother of a kid
who just signed up.

02:34.688 --> 02:38.226
- She's not ready.
- She thinks she is.

02:38.259 --> 02:41.462
- What do you think?
- [ Sighs ]

02:41.495 --> 02:44.164
What's wrong with the army?

02:45.933 --> 02:48.236
You can leave college.

02:48.269 --> 02:51.805
You can't sit up one day
in the army and say,

02:51.839 --> 02:54.275
"You know,
I want to go home."

03:01.615 --> 03:04.485
She's grown, darlin'.

03:04.518 --> 03:06.254
And she has left home.

03:23.136 --> 03:26.674
[ Gunfire ]

03:26.707 --> 03:29.243
[ Telephone Ringing ]

03:29.277 --> 03:32.413
Leave it.
I said, sir,
walk away.

03:32.446 --> 03:35.583
- All our personal information--
- Does it matter if the next
paper is your obituary?

03:35.616 --> 03:37.851
This building was hit
by a bomb two days ago.
Yeah, one bus.

03:37.885 --> 03:40.354
People have been stuck here.
Sick. Terrified.
Transporting eight souls.

03:40.388 --> 03:42.623
- Eight souls plus my team.
- Unable to make contact
with their loved ones.

03:42.656 --> 03:45.293
And you and your men show up,
order us to leave!

03:45.326 --> 03:47.728
We can't take any of our--
Mr. Ambassador, sir!

03:47.761 --> 03:51.198
Would you have rather
waited longer?
State Department did nothing!

03:51.231 --> 03:54.368
Why didn't they evacuate us,
transport us out of here when
this thing first happened?

03:54.402 --> 03:56.404
You couldn't get out.
The army couldn't get in.

03:56.437 --> 03:59.573
Chopper couldn't take off.
Bad weather. Too much
firepower on the ground.

03:59.607 --> 04:01.709
You think we were sitting
at the 7-Eleven next door?

04:01.742 --> 04:05.045
We had to muster up, fly in,
parachute in four miles away,

04:05.078 --> 04:09.283
hike in here, not get our
asses shot off, so we could
get your asses out.

04:09.317 --> 04:11.385
We are your last line
of defense, sir.
We are the cavalry.

04:11.419 --> 04:15.088
[ Artillery Exploding,
Gunfire ]

04:15.122 --> 04:17.558
Do you want out of Abidjan?
A safe ride home?

04:17.591 --> 04:20.628
- Of course I do!
- Good. While I organize a way
to get you out of here,

04:20.661 --> 04:23.297
you'd best have a chat
with your husband.

04:23.331 --> 04:27.335
Edward--
Don't tell me what to do.

04:27.368 --> 04:30.137
Stay calm. Their shells
are now falling way
beyond the embassy.

04:30.170 --> 04:32.773
Evac bus is almost ready.

04:32.806 --> 04:34.808
Unless you've been otherwise
directed to,

04:34.842 --> 04:36.877
please make your way
to the designated
upstairs safe area.

04:38.612 --> 04:43.984
[ Speaking French ]

04:44.017 --> 04:46.186
Will you abandon all of us?

04:46.219 --> 04:48.989
Will you abandon us
for not being American?

04:49.022 --> 04:50.958
We have a list.

04:52.860 --> 04:54.962
I'm sure that will
console the dead.

05:01.335 --> 05:03.937
It's moving northeast.
If it's over, we can stay.

05:03.971 --> 05:07.375
Mr. Ambassador, you stay,
we cannot guarantee
your safety.

05:07.408 --> 05:12.680
Edward, you stay if you want,
but I am telling you,
I am going with these men.

05:12.713 --> 05:16.684
You'd leave me here?
I'd listen to Sgt. Black,
whom you are attacking...

05:16.717 --> 05:20.020
[ Beeping ]
and accusing of abandoning us
when he came here to help.

05:20.053 --> 05:22.690
Sweetie--
Yeah?

05:22.723 --> 05:25.859
- Uh, 1100 hours, three or
four miles out. Hold one.
- Let it go.

05:25.893 --> 05:28.362
All right. Listen to me.

05:28.396 --> 05:31.198
Insurgents intercept us,
ask if you're with the
American Embassy, you say no,

05:31.231 --> 05:33.801
it's gonna be dandy
when they find your business
card in your pocket.

05:33.834 --> 05:36.236
Give me your passports,
all your personal I.D.

05:37.838 --> 05:40.240
Go.

05:40.273 --> 05:44.311
- Uh, I'm figuring 1330 latest
at the pickup point.
- This is not important.

05:44.344 --> 05:47.347
You get the truck.
Transpo you to the water.
All right. Roger.

05:47.381 --> 05:50.418
Now stick right on my tail.
Make me happy.

05:50.451 --> 05:53.387
I'll meet you, Dirt Diver,
our packages.
Shouldn't he come with us?

05:53.421 --> 05:55.723
He's making sure
no one comes after us.

05:55.756 --> 06:00.160
- Don't be long.
- I'm not on time,
I won't be coming.

06:00.193 --> 06:05.032
Stay below the windows.
The insurgents do not want
those native to Abidjan.

06:05.065 --> 06:07.367
They want the Americans.
We gotta hustle.

06:07.401 --> 06:10.070
We can't just leave
all the locals here.

06:10.103 --> 06:12.072
They're not at risk
once we're gone.

06:12.105 --> 06:14.341
Some of them were hurt
in the bombings.

06:14.374 --> 06:17.044
The insurgents will let in
medical care once they know
we're not here.

06:19.312 --> 06:22.916
I have a girlfriend.
We all have a girlfriend.

06:24.051 --> 06:26.920
Gotta wrap it up,
Mr. Kapp.

06:26.954 --> 06:29.823
Godspeed, all of you.

06:32.259 --> 06:34.428
You do whatever they
say to do, you hear me?

06:34.462 --> 06:36.997
I know this isn't a video game.
Okay, Dad?

06:41.902 --> 06:45.038
Yo, Bets.
Yo, Betsy.

06:45.072 --> 06:47.407
Hey, Ladybug.
Hang up, could you?

06:48.942 --> 06:52.546
Gotta go, Suze.
My dad.

06:52.580 --> 06:56.116
- I was on the phone.
- I can see.

06:56.149 --> 06:59.419
Just wanted to spend some time
with you before you went off
to Basic.

06:59.453 --> 07:01.989
Let's take a drive.
I just got up!

07:02.022 --> 07:04.858
Car works before noon.
Humor me.

07:06.326 --> 07:08.862
Leave 'em.
You won't need it.

07:21.008 --> 07:23.110
Put 'em all on.
Dad?

07:23.143 --> 07:25.946
I said put 'em on.
[ Scoffs ]

07:29.717 --> 07:32.052
Get out of the car.

07:34.888 --> 07:37.925
It's like 110 degrees.
It's even hotter
when you're hiking.

07:37.958 --> 07:39.860
You don't expect me
to go hiking?

07:39.893 --> 07:41.929
Camp is three miles
down this way.

07:41.962 --> 07:43.897
Follow the road.
Expect to see you there.

07:45.499 --> 07:48.068
[ Engine Starts ]

08:05.385 --> 08:08.956
Edgard! Hey,
he works with me.
Can he come?

08:08.989 --> 08:12.059
Sorry. No can do. Get moving!
Yeah, but he's
a friend of mine.

08:12.092 --> 08:14.828
This is not just about you.
It's about your s--
[ Glass Shattering ]

08:14.862 --> 08:16.964
God!
[ Screaming ]

08:16.997 --> 08:21.334
[ Groaning, Sighing ]

08:21.368 --> 08:24.171
Just when everything
was going so well.

08:24.204 --> 08:27.875
[ Man ]
* Give me your secrets
Bring me a sign *

08:27.908 --> 08:31.879
* Give me a reason
to walk the fire *

08:31.912 --> 08:33.914
* See another dawn

08:33.947 --> 08:36.149
* Through a daughter's eyes

08:36.183 --> 08:39.853
* You give me a reason
to walk the fire **

08:43.724 --> 08:46.259
There's our pony.
We're gonna ride it out
of here nice and easy.

08:46.293 --> 08:48.528
Clippity-clop.
My mates bring the others.

08:48.562 --> 08:50.564
August O'Neill.
My wife, Alice,
will be back soon.

08:50.598 --> 08:52.532
She has our daughter.
They're inside the embassy.

08:52.566 --> 08:55.335
No time for sightseeing.
The stress.
Her milk dried up.

08:55.368 --> 08:58.071
Eva's only six months old.
She went to find
evaporated milk.

08:58.105 --> 09:01.274
- You better hope there's
a cow in the lobby.
- Head count?

09:01.308 --> 09:04.511
- Save two, his wife and kid.
- You board last.
It's the longest we can wait.

09:04.544 --> 09:07.280
Maddy Shelette.
I'm Ambassador Blashek's
secretary.

09:07.314 --> 09:09.516
Maddy, were you able
to salvage any--
That's enough.

09:09.549 --> 09:12.953
- Don't listen to him.
- This'll probably go belly up
before it makes it 10 miles.

09:12.986 --> 09:16.523
We only need two.
Ellis Kapp and Jamie Kapp.

09:16.556 --> 09:19.059
Ambassador Blashek,
Mrs. Blashek on board.

09:19.092 --> 09:21.862
- Mr. O'Neill?
- I gotta wait for my family.

09:21.895 --> 09:26.199
- I don't, sir.
Please get on the bus.
- I'll find 'em and catch up.

09:26.233 --> 09:28.602
Whenever my mates ask you
to do anything, please comply.

09:28.636 --> 09:32.272
- Open the gate.
- I'll swing in, you're moving.

09:32.305 --> 09:35.475
- Stay low, stay quiet,
stay calm.
- [ Engine Sputtering ]

09:35.508 --> 09:38.912
Come on. Move over.
You flood this thing,
I don't got time to call AAA.

09:38.946 --> 09:42.382
You're a good, good bus.

09:42.415 --> 09:44.785
You are the prettiest bus
I've ever seen.

09:44.818 --> 09:47.254
If you were a woman,
I'd make you my own.
Yes, I would.

09:47.287 --> 09:50.223
[ Engine Starts ]

09:50.257 --> 09:52.259
[ Gunfire ]

09:52.292 --> 09:55.162
Go!

10:16.016 --> 10:20.754
[ Gunshots ]
[ Glass Shattering ]

10:20.788 --> 10:24.324
[ Gunshots ]

11:09.602 --> 11:14.507
- [ Explosion ]
- We hit an I.E.D.! Out!

11:14.541 --> 11:17.510
Everybody out!
Get off the bus!

11:19.947 --> 11:22.582
Everybody out!
Go, go, go!

11:22.615 --> 11:25.886
Get away!
Move down the fence line!

11:25.919 --> 11:28.088
[ Coughing ]
Help!

11:29.890 --> 11:31.859
Where's Maddy?

11:31.892 --> 11:33.894
Help! Help me!

11:33.927 --> 11:37.164
Help!

11:37.197 --> 11:39.532
Help me!

11:39.566 --> 11:42.402
You have to get out of the road.
She's got a fiancÃ©
back in the States.

11:42.435 --> 11:45.005
- Help! Help!
- Please come with me. Okay?

11:45.038 --> 11:50.277
- Maddy. Maddy.
- Help! Help!

11:50.310 --> 11:52.946
[ Gunfire ]

11:58.952 --> 12:02.389
- She gonna be okay?
- I can't see.
I can't see. I can't.

12:03.723 --> 12:05.859
I can't see.

12:05.893 --> 12:07.594
Get the compresses on.

12:11.799 --> 12:13.967
[ Coughing ]

12:14.001 --> 12:15.769
Rendezvous is at 1330.

12:17.805 --> 12:20.673
[ Explosion ]

12:26.013 --> 12:28.148
We gotta get off this road!

12:28.181 --> 12:30.417
We're going through the field.

12:30.450 --> 12:33.320
Grab her.
[ Sobbing ]

12:34.687 --> 12:36.689
Lean on me.
I got you.

12:38.758 --> 12:42.095
[ Gunfire ]

12:42.129 --> 12:43.931
That way. Let's move.
Come on.

12:46.599 --> 12:50.170
All of you single file on me.
Indian-style, one line.

12:50.203 --> 12:52.605
Where are we going?
Wait for the others.
Wait for the others.

12:52.639 --> 12:54.641
Let's move.
Let's move.
Let's go.

12:54.674 --> 12:56.709
All right.

13:01.614 --> 13:05.585
Come on!
We're moving too slow!

13:05.618 --> 13:07.988
- Get back in line!
What are you doing? Hey!
- It's open!

13:08.021 --> 13:10.290
Get in line!

13:11.859 --> 13:13.994
There they are.

13:14.027 --> 13:16.596
[ Explosion ]

13:16.629 --> 13:21.734
- [ Screaming ]
- [ Tires Skidding ]

13:26.673 --> 13:29.809
Do not move.

13:29.843 --> 13:32.612
What was his name?
That man.

13:32.645 --> 13:35.248
We didn't even know his name!

13:37.885 --> 13:40.187
Everybody out, my side now.

13:40.220 --> 13:42.355
Keep your heads down.
Keep your heads down.

13:42.389 --> 13:44.791
Behind that tanker, go!
[ Baby Crying ]

13:44.824 --> 13:46.860
Down!
[ Bullets Ricocheting ]

13:49.162 --> 13:53.566
Hammerhead, I've got resistance.

13:53.600 --> 13:55.869
You all might want
to hold still.

13:55.903 --> 13:58.038
We are in the middle
of a minefield.

14:00.707 --> 14:02.709
You happy now?

14:06.179 --> 14:10.918
It took you two hours
to walk three miles?
What'd you do?

14:10.951 --> 14:13.853
Stop and reapply
your makeup?
This isn't funny.

14:13.887 --> 14:16.089
You got that right.
This is serious business.

14:16.123 --> 14:19.092
How you get where you get,
how fast you get there.

14:19.126 --> 14:21.394
A statute mile is 5,280 feet.

14:21.428 --> 14:24.397
63,360 inches.

14:24.431 --> 14:27.200
Should take 2,000 steps
to walk a mile.

14:27.234 --> 14:29.869
Means you had
to take 6,000 steps.

14:29.903 --> 14:32.605
Person should be able
to walk a mile in 12 minutes.

14:32.639 --> 14:37.844
It took you 120 to do what
you should be able to do in 35.

14:37.877 --> 14:41.714
- So?
- So you're either lazy
or out of shape.

14:41.748 --> 14:43.783
- You lazy?
- No, I'm hungry.

14:43.816 --> 14:46.353
You know how to shoot.
Go rustle up some grub.

14:46.386 --> 14:50.057
This camp isn't gonna
be big enough for--
Excuse me. No, no, no.

14:50.090 --> 14:52.625
This hooch is mine.

14:52.659 --> 14:55.262
In your rucksack,
you got a canteen.
It's empty.

14:55.295 --> 14:57.931
But I bet you
you can find a water source.

14:57.965 --> 15:00.200
You also got a poncho
and a knife.

15:00.233 --> 15:04.071
Oh, yeah, and,
uh, there are rocks
all over here.

15:04.104 --> 15:06.239
All the basics for building
yourself a hooch.

15:06.273 --> 15:10.310
So I suggest you get up a move
on so you get it all done.

15:16.516 --> 15:18.952
Sun's going down.

15:18.986 --> 15:23.756
You hesitate,
it goes down sooner
because it feels offended.

15:29.262 --> 15:34.301
I make it 1145, which only
gives us about an hour
and 15 to traverse this lot.

15:34.334 --> 15:37.070
I'm willing to go on ahead.
I'll go.

15:37.104 --> 15:39.806
Do that, probably be
the last thing you ever do.
You're 17 years old.

15:39.839 --> 15:42.642
You can't do anything.
Mines are not our only problem.

15:42.675 --> 15:44.744
There are rebels out there.

15:44.777 --> 15:47.647
Seeing us moseying
across the space,
it's gonna make their week...

15:47.680 --> 15:50.250
to cut off our ears
and show 'em
to the folks back home.

15:50.283 --> 15:54.988
Mr. White?
What I tell you will be
precisely what you do.

15:55.022 --> 15:57.657
And what I tell you to do
ain't no request.

15:57.690 --> 16:00.027
Maddy,
I gotta help probe.
So I can't assist you.

16:00.060 --> 16:02.829
If you can carry
Maddy, great.

16:02.862 --> 16:07.034
If you can't,
put her feet on yours.

16:07.067 --> 16:11.038
Like when you danced
with your daddy
when you were a little girl.

16:11.071 --> 16:14.541
Don't move!
Not a step!

16:14.574 --> 16:16.676
But we gotta
get outta here fast.

16:16.709 --> 16:19.446
The only way is slow
and careful. The line.

16:19.479 --> 16:23.550
The line you're in now
is one you hold.
Not right, not left.

16:23.583 --> 16:27.220
The man says one step,
one step it is.

16:27.254 --> 16:29.289
You're a duck.
Your mama's leading the way...

16:29.322 --> 16:32.192
and you do what she says exactly
as she says it.

16:32.225 --> 16:33.926
[ Explosion ]
[ Gasps ]

16:35.062 --> 16:38.365
We need more probes--
Wood, if possible.

16:38.398 --> 16:40.533
Any of you have something
we can use as a probe?

16:40.567 --> 16:43.136
Ruler? Stick?

16:43.170 --> 16:46.139
I got a pen.

16:46.173 --> 16:48.408
Good. Pass it forward
to the ambassador.

16:48.441 --> 16:51.078
You, hold on to Maddy.

16:51.111 --> 16:55.715
Relay it hand over shoulder.
Don't turn around.

16:55.748 --> 16:58.518
Don't shift your weight.

16:58.551 --> 17:04.324
I have a nail file. When I--
We gave parties. I--
I always wanted my nails to--

17:04.357 --> 17:08.228
- Beth! I don't think they
care how you wanted to look!
- Thank you, Mrs. Blashek.

17:08.261 --> 17:10.197
You hold onto that.
I'm sure it'll be of use.

17:12.965 --> 17:15.235
We can't just stand here.

17:15.268 --> 17:17.737
They are gonna see us
and kill us eventually.

17:17.770 --> 17:20.340
You rather do it to
yourself right now?

17:20.373 --> 17:23.110
[ Sobbing ]

17:24.911 --> 17:28.548
[ Gunfire ]
[ Explosions ]

17:28.581 --> 17:30.750
You got guard duty.

17:30.783 --> 17:33.353
But climb it.
Don't just stand next to it.

17:33.386 --> 17:35.688
What? You afraid you're
gonna break a nail?

17:35.722 --> 17:38.891
Afraid I'll cut my hands.
Don't want an infection
in the woods now, do I?

17:38.925 --> 17:41.294
You're smart.

17:41.328 --> 17:46.399
You're so smart, do you know
what kind of mean critters
are indigenous to this area?

17:46.433 --> 17:50.203
Spiders. You gotta worry about
tarantulas, black widows,
brown recluses.

17:50.237 --> 17:52.872
All cunning little bastards.
And, of course, there's snakes.

17:52.905 --> 17:56.143
Forty-six species and subspecies
live around here.

17:56.176 --> 18:00.313
Five varieties of vipers.
Worst of them is a rattlesnake.

18:00.347 --> 18:04.717
But all vipers got vertical
slit pupils, not horizontal.

18:04.751 --> 18:08.255
- That's how you'll know.
- Yeah, but I don't expect
to see one up close.

18:08.288 --> 18:10.423
Turn it over.
Expect to see one.

18:10.457 --> 18:12.992
Stay alert.

18:16.296 --> 18:20.267
All right. Road's blocked.
We're gonna have to go by foot.

18:20.300 --> 18:23.636
To the rendezvous point?
No. Our job is to help
those people.

18:23.670 --> 18:26.306
We're all they got.

18:26.339 --> 18:28.675
Now the fools out there,
they got twitchy
trigger fingers.

18:28.708 --> 18:31.278
They find those folks,
they'll pick 'em off.

18:31.311 --> 18:34.347
I'm not gonna let my wife--
It's a minefield,
Mr. O'Neill.

18:34.381 --> 18:37.450
Those people are trapped.
Look, it's a catch-22.

18:37.484 --> 18:40.453
If they stay in that field,
they could get shot. They move
wrong, they step on a mine.

18:40.487 --> 18:42.655
Our job is to keep them out
of everyone's sight.

18:42.689 --> 18:46.092
What about the cost to us?
Yeah. There could be a cost
to everyone.

18:46.125 --> 18:49.962
But first,
we gotta help ourselves.
Create diversions.

18:49.996 --> 18:52.832
[ Gunfire ]
Keep the bad guys
focused on us.

18:52.865 --> 18:55.468
Lure the shooters towards us.
Towards us?

18:55.502 --> 18:58.505
If we appear to be a threat,
they won't have time
to get to our mates.

18:58.538 --> 19:01.441
That'll give those folks
time to get out.

19:01.474 --> 19:04.344
Look. We're gonna use that
car to create a diversion.

19:08.047 --> 19:09.982
[ Gunfire ]
You ever use one of these?

19:12.652 --> 19:15.188
All right. You got a trigger
finger you can use it.
Just point and shoot.

19:15.222 --> 19:17.490
There'll be a recoil,
but it won't hurt you.

19:17.524 --> 19:21.361
All right, anyone advances on
you or you see anyone coming
after us, shoot him.

19:23.430 --> 19:27.367
Come with me.
I'm not gonna leave my wife
and child.

19:27.400 --> 19:30.637
It's buddy call.
You and me are going
swimming, pal.

19:30.670 --> 19:34.774
Take this.
Gus, do it.

19:36.743 --> 19:40.480
Grab anything you can
outta that car that's gonna
give us some smoke.

19:40.513 --> 19:42.515
You?

19:42.549 --> 19:45.518
I'm gonna pretend
I work at a gas station
and do a little tinkering.

19:45.552 --> 19:48.255
On my go.
[ Baby Cries ]

19:48.288 --> 19:51.691
Go!
[ Gunfire ]

19:51.724 --> 19:54.327
You first. Gus! Go!

19:54.361 --> 19:56.028
[ Baby Crying ]

20:00.933 --> 20:03.403
All of you not probing,
keep watch.

20:03.436 --> 20:06.839
Start under your feet,
tool in your palm.

20:06.873 --> 20:12.845
Palm up.
Gently slide it in on
a diagonal into the ground.

20:12.879 --> 20:16.048
Probe in a six-inch direction
all around you.

20:16.082 --> 20:19.218
If you feel resistance, stop.

20:19.252 --> 20:23.956
Call out. Mark that spot
with a circle in the dirt.

20:23.990 --> 20:25.958
Even if you think you're clear,
do not take a step.

20:25.992 --> 20:27.860
We make that call.

20:27.894 --> 20:29.862
Aren't they all
the same size?

20:29.896 --> 20:32.131
Technology of murder's
pretty creative.

20:32.164 --> 20:34.634
Could be six inches across.
Maybe two.

20:34.667 --> 20:37.304
It could be booby-trapped,
another mine under it.

20:37.337 --> 20:40.039
So you disarm it?
No. We avoid 'em.

20:40.072 --> 20:43.876
- Are there mines bigger
than six inches?
- Jamie, stop asking questions.

20:43.910 --> 20:47.079
They're good questions.
We should all know them.

20:47.113 --> 20:49.282
Yup, it's this big around.

20:49.316 --> 20:52.419
It's for tanks.
Your worries are over.

20:52.452 --> 20:54.487
Why don't you sit
down right here.
I'm gonna help them.

20:54.521 --> 20:57.724
No! Look where she was
about to sit.

20:57.757 --> 20:59.959
It's a bounding mine.
Look closer.

20:59.992 --> 21:02.995
You see those four prongs
surrounding that little
piece of steel?

21:03.029 --> 21:05.932
It's a Bouncing Betty.

21:05.965 --> 21:08.901
You put your fanny on that,
it goes off, it kills
everybody within 30 feet.

21:08.935 --> 21:12.972
Look, a natural born leader
I know that you are, Mr. Kapp.

21:13.005 --> 21:16.609
But a good leader knows how
to surround himself with great
advisers and take their advice.

21:16.643 --> 21:20.146
- You follow?
- Yeah, I do. I do.

21:20.179 --> 21:22.114
You're her eyes and your eyes.

21:28.388 --> 21:30.390
Use the flare.

21:39.165 --> 21:42.001
Get outta here!

21:52.178 --> 21:55.147
Follow me. Run.

21:55.181 --> 21:57.517
Dirt Diver, Hammerhead,
it's Cool Breeze.

21:57.550 --> 22:01.554
Turn around.
I'm at your 2:00.

22:01.588 --> 22:03.956
[ Williams ]
What's your status?

22:03.990 --> 22:06.426
- I got the family and I got
the gist. What do you need?
- Probes.

22:09.496 --> 22:12.064
Yeah, I think
we can handle that.
[ Gunfire ]

22:12.098 --> 22:14.000
Harvest time.

22:27.246 --> 22:29.849
[ Gasps ]
You're dead three times over.

22:29.882 --> 22:33.152
You got bit by
a venomous spider.
You fell out of the tree.

22:33.185 --> 22:37.590
-The enemy heard you scream,
picked you off.
-There's no enemy out here, Dad.

22:37.624 --> 22:39.892
There's no enemy
in boot camp either--

22:39.926 --> 22:44.030
you don't count the drill
instructor trained to get
you ready for any scenario.

22:44.063 --> 22:47.333
- Just hold on. I ain't
having no fun here either.
- I think you're having a ball.

22:47.366 --> 22:49.602
Is that so?
Yeah. You're just trying
to discourage me,

22:49.636 --> 22:52.004
get me to wash out here
so I won't go!

22:52.038 --> 22:54.541
Or I'll be so whipped,
I'll wash out there!
It won't work!

22:54.574 --> 23:00.212
Miss Elizabeth Blane,
nobody knows better than me
that you won't wash out.

23:00.246 --> 23:03.282
-Then why are you
putting me through this?
-This ain't about passing Basic.

23:03.315 --> 23:06.218
This is about making you
the best you can be while
you're going through it...

23:06.252 --> 23:08.721
so it don't hit you so hard.

23:08.755 --> 23:10.723
This here is the meetin'
before the meetin'.

23:10.757 --> 23:13.359
Be all that you can be.

23:13.392 --> 23:16.663
This time stay awake.

23:23.235 --> 23:26.138
When I get them, hand 'em to
the person in front of me.

23:26.172 --> 23:29.776
That person takes one out,
passes the bundle front.

23:29.809 --> 23:32.244
Ready!

23:32.278 --> 23:38.084
NCAA tournament 1992,
Duke versus Kentucky,
2.1 seconds left.

23:42.354 --> 23:45.458
And Laettner hits a 17-footer
with no time left
on the clock.

23:45.492 --> 23:48.895
Duke, 104 to 103.

23:48.928 --> 23:52.331
- Hey, Jamie. Heads up.
- [ Williams ]
I said pass it forward.

23:52.364 --> 23:55.602
- [ Explosion ]
- [ Screams ]

23:59.539 --> 24:03.976
[ Coughs, Screams ]

24:04.010 --> 24:07.480
[ Crying ]

24:07.514 --> 24:10.617
- It just tore away from me.
- Maddy?

24:10.650 --> 24:12.585
- [ Coughing ]
- Come get me.

24:12.619 --> 24:16.355
- Maddy.
- [ Groaning ]

24:16.388 --> 24:20.493
- Come get me.
- Look, the mine hurt your leg.

24:20.527 --> 24:22.762
I can't get to you.
You gotta stop the bleeding.

24:22.795 --> 24:25.598
I can't see.
I don't know where I am.

24:25.632 --> 24:28.134
Take your belt off now.

24:28.167 --> 24:33.339
- [ Gasping ]
- Maddy, Tommy's waiting
for you at home.

24:33.372 --> 24:36.876
You can do this.
[ Groaning ]

24:36.909 --> 24:41.514
You gotta take your belt,
feel your left leg.
It's wet. That's blood.

24:41.548 --> 24:44.684
It's not serious.

24:52.592 --> 24:55.528
Come on.
Pull your belt off!
[ Groaning ]

24:57.396 --> 24:59.532
[ Gunfire ]

24:59.566 --> 25:02.569
Okay. All right.

25:02.602 --> 25:06.305
Now take your belt
and wrap it around
your leg above your knee.

25:06.338 --> 25:08.708
[ Gasping ]
Come on.

25:08.741 --> 25:11.177
Keep trying.

25:14.413 --> 25:17.316
Okay, now squeeze the belt.
Pull the belt tight.

25:17.349 --> 25:19.952
[ Sobs ]

25:21.754 --> 25:25.191
Now you feel that?
The bleeding stopped.

25:26.458 --> 25:30.597
You know we can't.
It's too late.

25:36.435 --> 25:38.671
[ Gasps ]

25:38.705 --> 25:43.375
[ Sobs ]
Hey, look at your baby.
Look at Eva.

25:43.409 --> 25:46.512
Maddy!
It's a bunch of idiots.

25:46.545 --> 25:50.016
Okay, it's a bunch of idiots.
Faces we'll never see. A country
in turmoil. Wages of war.

25:50.049 --> 25:53.519
Stupidity killed her.

25:53.552 --> 25:56.889
Hey! I need you to focus
and look at your baby.

25:58.490 --> 26:00.226
There you go. Okay.

26:01.794 --> 26:05.064
[ Gunfire ]
[ Baby Crying ]

26:08.668 --> 26:10.870
I-I-- I didn't think.

26:10.903 --> 26:14.406
You got that right.
So now you can help probe.

26:16.943 --> 26:19.411
This woman's death
is nothing to you?

26:19.445 --> 26:22.915
Every death is something to me!

26:22.949 --> 26:25.551
There's four of you here.
There's three more
of you out there!

26:25.584 --> 26:27.820
Counting us, that makes 10!

26:27.854 --> 26:31.924
That's 10 more deaths
that I don't want to count
on my rosary when I get home!

26:31.958 --> 26:36.829
Now, everybody,
carefully probe!

26:41.000 --> 26:42.802
[ Baby Crying ]
[ Explosion ]

26:46.205 --> 26:48.808
All right, follow me.
Stay down.

26:50.142 --> 26:53.813
Sit here. You. Okay.

26:53.846 --> 26:56.649
I need you to pull the pin
and throw this
in the direction I throw.

26:56.683 --> 26:59.351
Come on.

26:59.385 --> 27:02.755
Wait for it.

27:02.789 --> 27:05.624
Now!

27:07.860 --> 27:09.996
I said pull the pin.
[ Men Shouting ]

27:10.029 --> 27:12.832
Do something.

27:19.906 --> 27:22.809
- They all dead?
- No. One's still coming.
I'm gonna circle around.

27:22.842 --> 27:26.345
Lure him towards you.
You fire the second
I start running.

27:26.378 --> 27:29.281
Hey! Man-up.

27:29.315 --> 27:32.685
This guy sees me and nails
my ass, he'll barrel right
through you to your family.

27:32.719 --> 27:35.021
That'll be on your head.

27:35.054 --> 27:38.858
- Take it. Fire. Now!
- [ Gunshot ]

28:07.586 --> 28:09.188
That's the name of that song.

28:11.623 --> 28:15.862
Feel for it. Close your eyes.
Use your hands.

28:15.895 --> 28:18.998
- Rocks will talk to you.
- [ Grunts ]
I got something.

28:19.031 --> 28:22.068
- Use it.
- [ Screams ]

28:22.101 --> 28:25.704
Whoa!

28:25.738 --> 28:31.010
- [ Gasps ] I'm okay.
- Want me to come down
to get you?

28:31.043 --> 28:35.681
- No! I can do this!
- Look. It's hot. You're tired.
Your knees are rubbed raw.

28:35.714 --> 28:39.919
Just choose!
Do you want me to be the best
or do you want me to quit?

28:39.952 --> 28:43.255
-Ain't nothing to be
but the best.
-Then coach me, don't coddle me!

28:46.292 --> 28:49.295
It's not in your arms.
It's in your head.

28:49.328 --> 28:52.131
It's all about the rock.

28:52.164 --> 28:54.300
Solve the puzzle
of climbing the wall.

28:57.837 --> 29:01.207
I shot. My hands were sweaty.
The gun fell out of my hands.

29:01.240 --> 29:06.212
I didn't drop it.
I didn't freeze.

29:06.245 --> 29:08.414
Psychologically,
whatever we do, there's
always motive behind it.

29:08.447 --> 29:10.783
Forget to lock the door,
we didn't want it locked.

29:10.817 --> 29:12.985
You're okay,
something inside gets stolen.

29:13.019 --> 29:15.221
You drop a gun,

29:15.254 --> 29:17.589
didn't want to use it.

29:17.623 --> 29:19.792
I don't want my family hurt!
What do you expect?

29:19.826 --> 29:21.994
You bring 'em to Abidjan,
the most dangerous place
on earth.

29:22.028 --> 29:24.730
You think it was gonna be
a vacation? You think they
wouldn't be at risk?

29:24.763 --> 29:27.834
I don't know
what I was thinking.

29:27.867 --> 29:30.769
- I didn't want you and Eva
in danger.
- Hey, come here.

29:30.803 --> 29:33.940
I got friends in that lot.
And you got colleagues
out in the open.

29:33.973 --> 29:37.009
We got a rendezvous less
than an hour away and we only
have that hour to help!

29:37.043 --> 29:40.112
We miss that window
and we're all screwed.

29:40.146 --> 29:43.816
So, buddy, you better figure out
real fast what you're capable of
and what you're willing to do,

29:43.850 --> 29:46.218
because I'm not gonna carry your
ass for another second.

29:47.619 --> 29:50.389
You understand me?

30:02.201 --> 30:07.339
What's my time?
You don't count the mishaps,
47 minutes.

30:07.373 --> 30:11.210
- How long should it take?
- Experienced climber, 15.

30:11.243 --> 30:14.146
Gonna do it again.

30:19.818 --> 30:22.354
[ Jonas ]
You got enough
gas in the tank?

30:22.388 --> 30:25.357
What's after the best?
Second best.

30:25.391 --> 30:28.460
- Wouldn't want to do that.
- Of course not.

30:28.494 --> 30:30.529
[ Jonas ]
You're moving nicely,
baby.

30:40.172 --> 30:43.675
Put me on the clock.
You're on it.

30:45.077 --> 30:47.479
We tie one end to the grenade,

30:47.513 --> 30:49.581
then we wrap the line around
something stationary.

30:49.615 --> 30:52.551
A tree--
In our case, a pole.

30:52.584 --> 30:56.855
We tie the other end across
the other side of the street.

30:56.889 --> 30:59.758
We anchor the can.
Can I have the can, please?

30:59.791 --> 31:01.894
All right.

31:01.928 --> 31:04.696
Anchor the can,
slide the grenade in,

31:04.730 --> 31:08.034
and carefully pull the pin.

31:08.067 --> 31:11.770
Can will do
what your hand would've.
Holds the spoon down.

31:11.803 --> 31:17.343
Someone trips the line,
pops the grenade out,
unleashes the spoon. Kapow.

31:17.376 --> 31:22.081
What if they're firing as
they're coming towards us?
What if? They will be. Come on.

31:23.749 --> 31:27.453
[ Grunting ]

31:27.486 --> 31:30.889
Time.
25 minutes.

31:30.923 --> 31:33.359
[ Sighs ]
You're done.

31:33.392 --> 31:36.929
Could a man do it better?
Argument exists.

31:36.963 --> 31:39.631
Men are built different.

31:39.665 --> 31:41.968
Muscular-skeletal
systems incline them
to be better climbers.

31:42.001 --> 31:45.704
On the other hand, women
do better at high altitudes.

31:45.737 --> 31:48.874
- I'm sorry?
- You did a fine job.

31:48.907 --> 31:52.644
- Could a man do it better?
- Baby girl,
that's a losing fight.

31:52.678 --> 31:56.082
What do you care
what a man can do?
What can you do?

31:56.115 --> 31:59.986
You can slow down
your breathing. You can
take longer to exhale.

32:03.522 --> 32:06.458
I wouldn't trade you in
for any son in this world.

32:07.926 --> 32:10.529
And I think you're gonna be
one hell of a soldier.

32:12.598 --> 32:15.134
Smile.

32:21.707 --> 32:24.343
You thirsty or just crazy?
I did some scrounging.

32:24.376 --> 32:27.413
Found a few gas cans,
some oil, even an old
tin of turpentine.

32:27.446 --> 32:29.415
Figured we could use
some insurance.

32:29.448 --> 32:31.317
Worst thing about me,
I'm a smoker.
[ Vehicle Approaching ]

32:33.452 --> 32:35.354
You ready?
No.

32:35.387 --> 32:38.690
Shoot!

32:49.735 --> 32:51.337
Black!

32:53.339 --> 32:54.773
- [ Clicks ]
- [ Gunshot ]

32:54.806 --> 32:57.376
[ Groans ]

33:10.522 --> 33:13.825
[ Men Shouting ]

33:21.833 --> 33:24.203
You need to have
a nic fit more often.

33:24.236 --> 33:27.639
Molotov cocktail's a great idea.
What took you so long?

33:27.673 --> 33:32.811
I got stuck. Biggest decision
I ever made in my life
was where to go for dinner.

33:32.844 --> 33:36.848
I could only think in the way
I've thought all my life.
There was no outside the box.

33:36.882 --> 33:39.651
It's an outside the box
situation all right.
Yeah. Figured that one out.

33:39.685 --> 33:42.020
Getting slapped around
may have helped.

33:42.054 --> 33:45.023
Dirt Diver,
we're gonna come around
the quiet side of the lot,

33:45.057 --> 33:47.159
meet up at the transpo truck.

33:47.193 --> 33:49.027
Let's go get your family.

33:55.367 --> 33:58.104
Your bandana's wet.
You bleeding through?

33:58.137 --> 34:01.440
Nope. I doused it
in some canteen water.

34:01.473 --> 34:03.775
Found some evening primrose
for the swelling.

34:03.809 --> 34:07.446
Cattail for the cuts.
Who taught you about
medicinal plants?

34:07.479 --> 34:09.615
My daddy taught me
when I was young.

34:11.250 --> 34:16.788
I seem to recall.
My personal best,
fire-starting, 30 seconds.

34:16.822 --> 34:19.925
Oh, was that how long it took
you to shoot and skin
the hot dog too?

34:21.827 --> 34:24.830
You being nice to me now?
I'm always nice.

34:26.465 --> 34:29.801
Got an extra dog here.
You want it?
Uh-uh.

34:29.835 --> 34:31.903
Got a bigger fire.
Not now you don't.

34:31.937 --> 34:33.805
Grunt, get your butt over here.

34:39.010 --> 34:43.014
Permission to sit,
Sergeant Major?
R&R. An order.

34:48.754 --> 34:51.923
Had these
in the back of the truck.

34:57.296 --> 34:59.965
I ever tell you about
that time in Khartoum?

34:59.998 --> 35:02.934
Carlito decided to--
Take the spider home
to the states.

35:05.804 --> 35:08.674
How about the Caribbean, 1989?
Your appendix burst.
You were diving.

35:12.878 --> 35:15.881
Seems I told you
lots of stories.

35:22.321 --> 35:24.523
What is it you want to hear?

35:25.657 --> 35:27.726
All of it, Papa.

35:32.063 --> 35:37.002
[ Gunfire ]

35:38.570 --> 35:43.041
[ Explosion ]

35:43.074 --> 35:46.044
You said you'd come save us.
You walked us into this lot!

35:46.077 --> 35:48.480
Get the hell down!

35:50.349 --> 35:52.884
What'd you do?
You got a girl killed.

35:52.918 --> 35:55.521
Left you out there, you would've
died in the embassy,

35:55.554 --> 35:58.990
out in the street,
or running across this lot!

35:59.024 --> 36:03.395
We have a 14-year-old daughter
in Switzerland in school.

36:03.429 --> 36:06.097
Elena.
It'll be okay.

36:08.400 --> 36:11.270
We'll get you reunited.
It's our job.

36:13.239 --> 36:16.107
Step!
All right.
Let's skirt the perimeter.

36:28.254 --> 36:30.622
Step!

36:33.925 --> 36:37.396
[ Artillery, Gunfire ]

36:37.429 --> 36:40.232
They ain't done.

36:40.266 --> 36:43.502
So Orion's Belt. It's
the only one you taught me.

36:43.535 --> 36:47.172
I taught you more
than that.
Don't remember.

36:47.205 --> 36:50.141
Reach for it.

36:51.577 --> 36:53.745
Big Dipper.

36:55.113 --> 36:59.217
- Pole star.
- Big Dipper's
below the horizon.

36:59.251 --> 37:02.288
What's on the other side?

37:02.321 --> 37:06.425
Cass-- Cassie--

37:06.458 --> 37:08.694
Cassiopeia.

37:08.727 --> 37:10.762
Lady in the chair.

37:12.298 --> 37:14.466
The big "W."

37:14.500 --> 37:18.537
What happened in Algiers?

37:18.570 --> 37:21.139
Ranger's Creed.

37:21.172 --> 37:25.277
"Leave no man behind." I know.
You couldn't get to him without
endangering everyone else,

37:25.311 --> 37:28.614
and he was dying, right?

37:28.647 --> 37:31.750
Yeah. He wouldn't
have made it.

37:31.783 --> 37:33.819
But it was Algiers.

37:37.022 --> 37:39.591
They're the masters of torture.

37:39.625 --> 37:44.596
Imagine if someone
asked you what your major
accomplishment was in life,

37:44.630 --> 37:50.235
and you said,
"I invented the most inhumane
torture techniques."

37:50.268 --> 37:53.004
What a legacy.

37:53.038 --> 37:57.142
They'd found him alive
in that minefield,

37:57.175 --> 37:59.177
they'd have put him through
hell before they killed him.

37:59.210 --> 38:02.614
So you-- What?

38:02.648 --> 38:06.818
Did what I had to.
You shot him.

38:06.852 --> 38:10.322
As I'd hoped they'd
do for me.

38:10.356 --> 38:13.191
That act of grace.

38:13.224 --> 38:15.327
- Get down!
- [ Screams ]
- [ Explosion ]

38:15.361 --> 38:20.165
Hey, we are 20 feet from safety.
I say we run for it.

38:20.198 --> 38:23.001
No. Slow
and steady wins the race.
We have a woman here!

38:23.034 --> 38:26.872
You have a son here!

38:26.905 --> 38:29.307
They're heading for us.

38:29.341 --> 38:31.877
We are just about out of time.
And I am out of patience.

38:36.582 --> 38:42.287
Toe popper! Lot of good
you've done us or your kid!

38:42.320 --> 38:46.224
There is heroic
and there is stupid,
and you keep choosing stupid!

38:46.257 --> 38:48.527
I am not gonna die for you!

38:48.560 --> 38:52.398
And I am not gonna sacrifice
these people that have
come this far already!

38:52.431 --> 38:54.566
Look at your son!
Look at him!

38:54.600 --> 38:59.805
Brave kid! No trouble,
not one step of the way!

38:59.838 --> 39:03.909
That's heroism!
Now we are gonna probe
the rest of the way...

39:03.942 --> 39:06.044
just as carefully
as when we came in!

39:06.077 --> 39:11.182
- My mates and I are gonna get
you out of here if you listen!
- [ Screams ]

39:12.951 --> 39:15.921
[ Explosions, Gunfire ]

39:15.954 --> 39:18.857
[ Sobbing ]

39:18.890 --> 39:22.494
"Our Father, who art in heaven,
hallowed be thy name.

39:22.528 --> 39:24.062
Thy kingdom come,
thy will be done, on Earth--"

39:29.935 --> 39:32.571
It's ours!

39:34.906 --> 39:38.043
[ Man ]
Move! Move! Pershing! Jones!
Get up front!

39:38.076 --> 39:40.011
Find those mines!
Our ride's here.

39:40.045 --> 39:42.113
Expedite!

39:42.147 --> 39:47.052
- Call it out.
- Sixty-three, 64.

39:47.085 --> 39:50.456
-Lock those elbows, you come up.
-How long we gonna be
doing these?

39:50.489 --> 39:53.459
- Until I get tired.
- Dad. Dad, don't move.

39:53.492 --> 39:55.861
What? Throws you off?
I didn't say stop.

39:55.894 --> 39:57.896
[ Gunshot ]

40:12.077 --> 40:16.147
- Vertical split pupils.
- [ Laughs ]

40:16.181 --> 40:19.485
You signed up to be a regular
grunt, right?

40:19.518 --> 40:21.319
Yeah. Start out just like
my dad. Work my way up.

40:24.790 --> 40:27.759
You can do better.

40:27.793 --> 40:29.728
You got it in you
to be a leader.

40:29.761 --> 40:32.130
You're a leader.
Yes, I am.

40:32.163 --> 40:37.135
- But you're officer material.
- I don't want to be
a gut-eater, pushing papers.

40:37.168 --> 40:39.838
Nah. There's more to it
than that.

40:39.871 --> 40:42.608
If you're an officer,
you can make changes,
live better.

40:42.641 --> 40:44.610
Make a difference.
Be your boss.

40:44.643 --> 40:48.146
Oh, let's not engage
in fantasy.

40:48.179 --> 40:52.283
Look, you saved my life.
Which means I owe you.

40:52.317 --> 40:55.787
So I'm gonna give you a gift
it's taken me 25 years to learn.

40:55.821 --> 40:59.157
- Well, I hope it's expensive.
- It's expensive
you don't learn it.

41:02.561 --> 41:05.764
I'm gonna teach you
how to say good-bye
to your mother...

41:05.797 --> 41:08.366
without getting an emotional
frying pan upside your head.

41:16.542 --> 41:20.712
No one knows what they're made
of faced with a test.
You should be proud of him.

41:20.746 --> 41:25.684
He passed
with flying colors.
I am.

41:30.556 --> 41:33.191
Maybe you should tell him.

41:49.174 --> 41:51.409
Here.
Give me your wallet.

41:51.442 --> 41:53.579
I saw you take it
when you left home.

41:56.514 --> 41:59.017
Eight miles to the nearest
town, Euclid.

41:59.050 --> 42:02.253
You know your cardinal points?
Uh, north, east,
south, west.

42:02.287 --> 42:06.524
Good. All right.

42:06.558 --> 42:09.160
Due north, two miles,
follow this road.

42:09.194 --> 42:12.363
Then turn to 35 degrees
the rest of the way.
All right.

42:12.397 --> 42:15.601
See you there.
Not likely.

42:15.634 --> 42:19.370
I'm going home, and that's
18 miles beyond Euclid.

42:19.404 --> 42:23.374
- How am I supposed to make it
all that way with no money?
- I can think of four ways. Hmm.

42:23.408 --> 42:27.846
Thievin', hookin',
hikin' and thinkin'.

42:27.879 --> 42:30.448
See you when you get home.

42:41.259 --> 42:45.797
Where should she be by now?
Euclid.

42:45.831 --> 42:49.434
Trying to find a way
to get a lift here.
She'll be along.

42:49.467 --> 42:52.470
You leave our daughter
in the middle of nowhere,
26 miles from home.

42:52.503 --> 42:55.373
You want me to brush my teeth,
hop into bed, no worries?

42:55.406 --> 42:58.143
You can worry if you want to.
I'm going to bed.

42:58.176 --> 43:01.146
Don't expect anything
in that arena.

43:05.316 --> 43:09.387
I'd have been here faster,
but selling your body
takes up a lot of time.

43:09.420 --> 43:12.057
And why is that?

43:12.090 --> 43:15.093
Well, you need a marketing
plan, a decision tree,
like any business.

43:15.126 --> 43:17.262
I am so glad you dropped
out of college.

43:17.295 --> 43:20.298
Good night, Blane women.

43:27.038 --> 43:30.241
Baby, let me make you
something to eat,
get you some fresh--

43:30.275 --> 43:32.310
Oh, you know what, Ma?

43:32.343 --> 43:35.613
When Dad gives me back
my money, how about
I take you out to dinner?

43:35.647 --> 43:37.683
We can rent a scary,
jumpie-outie movie,

43:37.716 --> 43:40.819
curl up on the couch,
and just be one with nature.

43:40.852 --> 43:43.021
[ Laughs ]

43:44.389 --> 43:47.125
How'd you get back so soon?
Hitchhiking.

43:47.158 --> 43:49.327
Isn't that
a little dangerous?
Not if you're armed.

43:49.360 --> 43:53.031
- I stole Dad's gun
out of his rucksack.
- Does he know you took it?

43:53.064 --> 43:56.167
I assume so.

43:56.201 --> 43:59.404
So, what did you learn
in the woods?

44:00.638 --> 44:02.473
I'm gonna like the army.
